column5: Hey Guys and Gals, I'm buying a new prop in the next couple weeks and I'm just looking for a good/cheap place to get one. If anyone has good dealings with an online store or place around Cambridge let me know.  Thanks, Dan
Dan I got a good deal on a second prop for my boat on ebay. You might want to have a look there first. You never know there might be one for  you at a good price.
CITYWIDE WELDING in  MISSISSAUGA ON DREW RD.  I find them to be fair if they have what you need.  THEY also do repairs for a good price .  good luck   KEITH.
x 2 if you are going stainless. As well, check out Maximum Marine in Ancaster he has a wall full of props.
Thanks guys, and yes I'm going stainless
Dan what size are you looking for?J and J MArine in HAgersville is great as well!
Hey Dan,  Let me know what you are looking for.I am going to see James at maximum tomorrow and will see what they have.
I'm a tad late but I'm looking for a 13.75 x 15 or 13.75 x 16
I got a spare prop from Jim at J and J near Hagersville for a good price. Jim is very knowledgeable and a good guy guy to deal with. Ive sent a few friends his way with no complaints so far.
I will check them out, thanks
J and J may be able to fix your old prop.  They are amazing.  If it is the same guy he used to be near the French river, so lots of practice and he saved us several times. Michael
Current prop is fine, just want a 2nd
X3 City Wide Welding Inc  1867 Drew Rd, Mississauga, ON L5S 1J5 905-677-0316
Check out iboats.com. You may be able to score a deal there. And x4 on Citywide welding in Mississauga, I've heard nothing but good things about them.
